Rotarian London-Lagos Charity motorbike rider, Kunle Adeyanju earlier this evening gave an update on his Twitter handle on his experience with his Malian hosts. Adeyanju who started his who started his charity ride from London on April 19, is currently in Mali as he continues to pass the message about Polio in Nigeria and Africa as a whole.
Now in Mali, and preparing to enter Ivory Coast, it is obvious that Adeyanju is enjoying himself in Mali if he has been posting on his Twitter page is anything to go.
Adeyanju daily updates about his motorbike (Eagle) adventure on his Twitter handle, which commences from London some couple of weeks ago, have attracted a lot of attention from social media users across the world, with many Nigerians hilariously notifying him that they are ready to ride back with him to London if he wants to follow the same route while going back.
Adeyanju who awed his followers with most of his dangerous and spooky Sahara Desert experiences last week, attracted criticism from Mauritius authorities after he reported ill-treatment by officials.



